<p>Despite the migration of a significant section of the population to the southern plains or terai in recent years, the majority of the population still lives in the central highlands. The northern mountains are sparsely populated.</p>
<p>Kathmandu, with a population of around 800,000 (metropolitan area: 1.5 million), is the largest city in the country.</p>
<p><a name="Religion" id="Religion"></a></p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline">Religion</span></h3>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:IMG_0469_Kathmandu_Pashupatinath.jpg" class="image" title="Shaiva-devotees gather at the Hindu Pashupatinath Temple"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/IMG_0469_Kathmandu_Pashupatinath.jpg/250px-IMG_0469_Kathmandu_Pashupatinath.jpg" width="250" height="167" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
