<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> According to Interim Constitution <a href="/wiki/Nepali_language" title="Nepali language">Nepali</a> is only the official language (article 5, point 2). Other languages spoken as the mother tongue in Nepal are the national languages (article 5, point 1). According to article 5, point 3, all languages are accepted as official languages at the regional level. Besides, this part of the article is about native names and not about official language. The constitution does not state that Nepal written in Devanagari is the official name. <a href="http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Nepal_Interim_Constitution2007.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Nepal_Interim_Constitution2007.pdf" rel="nofollow">Nepal_Interim_Constitution2007</a></li>
